  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Refining UI Hierarchy**\n\nI\'ve realized that applying `min-h-screen bg-slate-900` to both `App.tsx` and child routes like `AdminDashboard`, `MasterDashboard`, and `Login` creates background overlapping issues. The child route backgrounds obscure the parent\'s. I\'m reassessing where these styles should reside to ensure the intended visual hierarchy.\n\n\n**Analyzing Height Expansion**\n\nI\'m now focusing on how `min-h-screen` behaves when content overflows the viewport. It seems the height expands correctly to encompass the content, which means the initial issue might stem from the application of `min-h-screen` across multiple components, specifically `App.tsx` and child routes like `AdminDashboard`. The critical observation is that if a child route, like the `AdminDashboard`, has its own `min-h-screen`, and the content exceeds this height, it should correctly expand, right? If so, why is there a visual issue? I\'m going back to the basics of the visual structure.\n\n\n"
